name: reverse_geocoder
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "reverse_geocoder" %}
{% set version = "1.5.1" %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 2a2e781b5f69376d922b78fe8978f1350c84fce0ddb07e02c834ecf98b57c75c

build:
  number: 0
  noarch: python
  script: "{{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . -vv"

requirements:
  host:
    - numpy >=1.11.0
    - python >=3.5
    - pip
  run:
    - numpy >=1.11.0
    - python >=3.5
    - scipy >=0.17.1

test:
  imports:
    - reverse_geocoder
  commands:
    - pip check
  requires:
    - pip

about:
  home: https://github.com/thampiman/reverse-geocoder
  license: LGPL-2.1-only
  license_family: LGPL
  license_file: LICENSE
  summary: 'Fast, offline reverse geocoder'
  description: |
    A Python library for offline reverse geocoding. It improves on an existing library called reverse_geocode developed by Richard Penman.

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - thewchan
